<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.516/53: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-30T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                        1921—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>102. Your 86, April 23, 5 p.m. If American banks subject themselves to
                            regulations of March 23, 1920, will they be permitted legally and
                            actually to join syndicate of paying banks in Poland, or will they be
                            obliged to liquidate completely?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>